{"questionId":"9085019","questionHtml":"<p>Show that the collision is elastic.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>Use of conservation of momentum. ✓<br>Rebound speed = 2.16 «m s<sup>−1</sup>» ✓<br>Calculation of initial KE = «<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math> × 0.800 × 4.317<sup>2</sup>» = 7.46 « J » ✓<br>Calculation of final KE = «<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math> × 0.800&nbsp; × 2.16<sup>2 </sup>+ <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math> × 2.40 × 2.16<sup>2</sup>» = 7.46 «J» ✓<br>«hence elastic»</p>","meta":{"questionId":"9085019","referenceCode":"23M.2.SL.TZ1.1bi","subjectId":"59-dp-physics-first-assessment-2025","title":"Show that the collision is elastic.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"i","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 4]","breadcrumbLabels":["A. Space, time and motion","A.2 Forces and momentum","A. Space, time and motion","A.3 Work, energy and power"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}